# Code Review Analysis Tool 🔍

## Purpose
This rule provides automated code review analysis based on project standards when triggered by the `!review` command.

## Trigger
- `!review` - Analyzes code changes in the current branch against project standards
- Case variations: `!REVIEW`, `!Review`, etc.

## Analysis Scope
When `!review` is triggered, the tool will:
1. Identify all modified files in the current branch (including staged and unstaged changes)
2. Analyze code changes against project standards:
   - [project-standards.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/project-standards.mdc)
   - [godoc-english-only.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/godoc-english-only.mdc)
3. Generate a comprehensive review report

## Analysis Areas 🎯

### 1. Architecture Compliance 🏗️
- Clean Architecture layer separation
- Dependency direction validation
- Core layer dependency constraints
- Proper use of ports and adapters pattern

### 2. Go Standards 📝
- Import formatting (goimports compliance)
- Function and variable naming conventions
- Error handling patterns
- Context usage
- Line spacing rules
- Constructor and dependency injection patterns
- Cross-package reference validation (variables/constants within same package)

### 3. Documentation Quality 📚
- GoDoc documentation presence for exported functions
- English-only GoDoc compliance
- Documentation completeness for complex functions
- Proper GoDoc formatting

### 4. Code Quality 💎
- SOLID principles adherence
- DRY principle compliance
- Return early pattern usage
- Proper error wrapping with context
- Security and validation practices

### 5. Testing Standards 🧪
- Test coverage for new/modified functions
- Table-driven test patterns
- Mock usage and dependency injection in tests

